* Zyber stretched atop the rock she had been sitting on for a bit, her 
muscles cramped from the cold night air.
Well, she had seen enough and it was about time that she was on her way.
With a sigh she set off towards her northern home once again, knowing that 
it would still be a while until she reached her humble abode.
The trees easily passed by as she continued to walk through the forest, the 
night air sending her the smell of game to the far north/east.
If she happened to come across that prey on her way home she would hunt, but 
if she didn't then she would simply continue her fast until she reached her 
den.
Zyber's coat glimmered silver in the light of the moon, giving her that 
ghostly appearense.
Her mind wondered as she traveled through the thick trees, wondering just 
what Rowdy could be up to at the moment.
But soon her mind narroed to getting home once again, picking up her pace.*
